Documented the Google Takeout workflow in the README: run [`galbum`](https://github.com/jackal998/google-album-metadata) first to write the `.json` sidecar metadata (original date / GPS) back into the media files, then scan — so Takeout photos date and dedupe correctly instead of landing in `UNDATED`. Records that #471's scanner-side sidecar matching is superseded by the standalone galbum tool. ([#471](https://github.com/jackal998/photo-manager/issues/471))
